# CloudWatch Alarm → AWS DevOps Agent Webhook Integration

This project deploys a **fully automated integration between CloudWatch alarms and AWS DevOps Agent investigations** using AWS CloudFormation.

When a CloudWatch alarm enters the **ALARM state**, this solution automatically triggers an **AI-powered investigation** through the AWS DevOps Agent webhook.

The integration performs the following:

1. Detects **CloudWatch alarm state changes**
2. Enriches the alarm with configuration and metric data
3. Builds an **incident payload**
4. Signs the payload using **HMAC SHA-256**
5. Sends the payload to the **AWS DevOps Agent Generic Webhook**

---

# Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR

CW[CloudWatch Alarm] -->|State Change| EB[EventBridge Rule]

EB -->|Invoke| L[Lambda Function]

L -->|DescribeAlarms| CWAPI[CloudWatch API]
L -->|GetMetricStatistics| METRIC[Metric Data]
L -->|Read Secret| SM[Secrets Manager]

L -->|Build Payload + HMAC Signature| WH[DevOps Agent Webhook]

WH --> AI[AWS DevOps Agent\nAutomated Investigation]
```

---

# Features

## Automatic Incident Creation

When a CloudWatch alarm transitions to **ALARM**, the Lambda function automatically generates a structured **incident payload** and sends it to AWS DevOps Agent.

---

## Alarm Enrichment

The Lambda function enriches the event with additional information:

- Alarm configuration
- Alarm tags
- Latest metric datapoints
- AWS account ID
- AWS region
- Alarm threshold configuration

This provides the DevOps Agent with **complete investigation context**.

---

## Tag-Based Filtering

Only alarms tagged with:

```
auto_investigate=true
```

will trigger investigations.

This allows teams to **control which alarms trigger automated analysis**.

---

## Environment-Based Priority

The alarm **env tag** determines the priority of the incident.

| Tag | Priority |
|----|----|
| prod | CRITICAL |
| uat | MEDIUM |
| dev | LOW |

---

## Secure Webhook Authentication

The webhook request uses **HMAC SHA-256 authentication**.

Signature format:

```
HMAC_SHA256(timestamp:payload)
```

Headers sent to the webhook:

```
Content-Type: application/json
x-amzn-event-timestamp: <timestamp>
x-amzn-event-signature: <signature>
```

Webhook credentials are stored securely in **AWS Secrets Manager**.

---

# CloudFormation Resources

This stack deploys the following infrastructure.

| Resource | Purpose |
|--------|--------|
| Secrets Manager Secret | Stores webhook URL and secret |
| Lambda Function | Processes alarms and sends webhook |
| IAM Role | Permissions for Lambda |
| EventBridge Rule | Captures CloudWatch alarm events |
| Lambda Permission | Allows EventBridge to invoke Lambda |

---

# Deployment

## Prerequisites

- AWS CLI configured
- CloudFormation permissions
- Existing AWS DevOps Agent webhook endpoint

---

## Deploy the stack

```bash
aws cloudformation deploy \
--template-file template.yaml \
--stack-name devops-agent-alarm-integration \
--capabilities CAPABILITY_NAMED_IAM \
--parameter-overrides \
WebhookUrl=https://event-ai.us-east-1.api.aws/webhook/generic/YOUR_WEBHOOK_ID \
WebhookSecret=YOUR_WEBHOOK_SECRET
```

---

# Required Alarm Tags

For an alarm to trigger automated investigations, it must include the following tags.

```
auto_investigate = true
env = prod | uat | dev
```

Example:

```
Key: auto_investigate
Value: true

Key: env
Value: prod
```

